    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>Plans for the M.T.A.</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Luiz S Homem de Mello letter on May 4 editorial says street parkers should be charged market rates to help finance New York City subway improvements</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Your May 4 editorial ''Ambitious Plans for Transit'' is correct that ''more financing will be needed from other sources.'' One other source is to charge for parking on the streets at all times and at market rates.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Your May 4 editorial ''Ambitious Plans for Transit'' is correct that ''more financing will be needed from other sources.'' One other source is to charge for parking on the streets at all times and at market rates.</p>
        <p>The subway and the streets are public resources. If riders have to pay to use the subway, drivers should also have to pay to store their property on the streets.</p>
        <p>LUIZ S. HOMEM DE MELLO  New York, May 4, 2000</p>
      </block>
    </body.content>
